---
description: Local developer memory retrieval and persistence behavior
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

Always retrieve context before major coding tasks.

Before any non-trivial implementation (architecture, auth, data model, core logic):
1) call `begin_task_context` with task + task_type (+ optional project_id)
2) use retrieved context to guide changes

Default `project_id` resolves to the current workspace automatically.
Recommended `task_type`: `feature`, `bugfix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `ops`, or `auto`.

Use `get_context_packet` only when you need lower-level/debug retrieval output.

If user expresses a stable preference:
call `save_memory` with `memory_type=dev_preference`.

If a project convention emerges:
call `save_memory` with `memory_type=project_convention`.

If an architecture decision is made:
call `log_decision` with clear rationale.

Only save memories that are durable and likely useful in future sessions.
Do not auto-save uncertain or temporary observations.

Never save secrets (keys, tokens, credentials).
